<p>
This is Freecell Solver - a program that automatically solves layouts of
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FreeCell">Freecell</a> and similar
variants of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solitaire">Card
Solitaire</a> such as Eight Off, Forecell, and
Seahaven Towers, as well as
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simple_Simon_%28solitaire%29">Simple
Simon</a> boards. Freecell Solver is
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open_source_software">free
and open source software</a> freely available under the
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License">MIT/Expat License</a>.
It can be <a href="$(ROOT)/js-fc-solve/text/">used online</a> (which
requires a modern enough web browser with JavaScript support),
or <a href="$(ROOT)/download.html">downloaded</a> either as
Microsoft Windows 32-bit binaries, or as the C source distribution.
</p>

<p>
Included with the archive are programs that can automatically
provide the starting layouts of several popular Solitaire Implementations.
</p>

<p>
Freecell Solver can also be built as a library for use within your own
Solitaire implementations. A more detailed list of features can be found
in the <a href="features.html"><b>Features List</b></a>.
</p>

